replies.body:
might I add a few picks to that list:

{{champion:113}} 
Sejuani is a great teamfight champion with decent damage, mobility, tankiness and tons of cc. She's good for initiating, peeling, catching and chasing, and she's very well rounded. She's a bit weak early but come midgame you'll be invaluable to your team and lategame you're nigh unkillable.
{{item:1413}} {{item:3742}}{{item:3065}}{{item:3025}}{{item:3800}}  {{item:3111}} 

{{champion:31}}
 When building as a tank, you become a meaty monster that can peel really well against assassins with a big aoe silence and offers some decent pick and teamfight potential with his long ass knockup and slowing q. He's got a decent, though mana hungry laning phase, tank stats, true damage, a second smite, sustain, waveclear and poke. When building like this it's important to understand you won't do well against anyone with lifesteal but on the plus side cho'gath is extemely good at freezing and laning like that, so it'll be a fairly irritating laning phase for your opponent unless they try to be really aggressive and towerdive you and that usually won't end well for them. Lategame you just walk around and laugh at the enemy trying to harm you.
