{{champion:89}} 
Praise the stun. When it comes to offensive/defensive peel there isn't much better than leona. She lacks sustain and she does rely on her adc to trigger her passive like braum but when it comes to tankiness in early kill lanes, outside of an ulting alistair, nothing comes close and moving into lategame teamfights, her ult can be devastating, as well as the surprising amount of followup damage she can offer beyond the initiation. 3 very long stuns and a slow, if you want to feel that you are making 'the plays' and carrying the team, she's one of the best tank supports out there.
